  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      POEM has recently described as an alternative treatment for achalasia in humans. In this
      procedure the esophageal sphincter is incised through a submucosal tunnel in the esophagus.
      In this study we aim to perform POEM on achalasia patients.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
